comments: Curry (GSW) firms up in Sabonis' (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
Vezenkov (SAC) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact with Green (GSW) during the driving shot attempt.
Looney (GSW) momentarily rests and removes his hands from Sabonis' (SAC) left arm and the marginal contact dissolves as the ball comes off of the rim.
Huerter (SAC) lowers his arm down and makes direct contact with the ball, dislodging it from Looney's (GSW) grasp.
Huerter (SAC) reaches for the ball and makes illegal contact with Looney's (GSW) head while the offensive player is on the ground with the ball.
Vezenkov (SAC) clamps and pulls Wiggins' (GSW) left arm, which affects his range of motion during the rebounding opportunity.
Although Curry (GSW) makes contact with the ball, he reaches across Fox's (SAC) and initiates illegal contact to his arm and wrist.
Sabonis (SAC) briefly rests his hand on Looney's (GSW) left arm and then removes the marginal contact as the rebound bounces away from both players.
Huerter (SAC) brings his right arm out and around Curry (GSW), initiating illegal contact with Curry's head and dislodging him during the screen.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in Curry's (GSW) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Curry (GSW) releases his pass and comes together with Monk (SAC) at the same spot on the floor and the contact is marginal.
After the ball becomes loose, Monk (SAC) comes together with Wiggins (GSW) and the contact is incidental.
Sabonis (SAC) and Looney (GSW) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.

Looney's (GSW) right arm is not in a legal vertical position when arm contact occurs with Fox, affecting his driving shot attempt. The shooting foul should have been assessed to Looney instead of Wiggins (GSW).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Green's (GSW) pass goes out of bounds and Green is the last player to touch the ball. Possession is properly awarded to Sacramento.
Fox (SAC) loses his footing and begins going to the ground on his own accord during his drive when Green (GSW) extends his hand toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with Fox's arm.
Wiggins (GSW) goes to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Fox (SAC).
Sabonis' (SAC) hand briefly comes to rest on Wiggins' (GSW) side as he establishes screening position and the contact during the inbound is marginal.
Prior to any potentially illegal contact from Green (GSW), Sacramento calls and is awarded a timeout.
Curry (GSW) and Vezenkov (SAC) engage as they move together off-ball and the contact is marginal.
Wiggins (GSW) moves alongside Monk (SAC) and pulls his forearm away as Monk gathers the ball and enters his upward shooting motion. The contact during the jump shot attempt is marginal.

Fox (SAC) moves alongside of Curry (GSW) and incidental foot to foot contact occurs, which results in Fox falling to the floor.  Curry braces for the ensuing contact with a collapsed forearm, which he does not extend into Fox to dislodge him from his defensive position.
Vezenkov (SAC) closes out in front of Curry (GSW) and marginal lower body contact occurs after the release as both players return to the floor.
